<HEADLINE>
<P>
MUSLIMS, CROATS MEET TO PLAN BOSNIA UNION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bosnian government and Croatian delegates opened talks Friday at the U.S. 
Embassy on drafting a constitution for a confederated state planned for their 
people in Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
</P>
<P>
 The plan, which is part of a rapprochement between the allies-turned-enemies, 
is seen as a major step toward peace in Bosnia. 
</P>
<P>
 A framework for the plan was signed by political leaders earlier this week in 
Washington. 
</P>
<P>
 U.S. officials brokering the accord hope that it will end all Muslim-Croat 
hostilities. 
</P>
