WILSON CALLS SPECIAL ELECTION FOR NOLAN'S SEAT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gov. Pete Wilson on Friday called a special election to fill the vacancy 
created in the 43rd Assembly District as a result of incumbent Pat Nolan's 
guilty plea in a Capitol corruption probe. 
</P>
<P>
 The district covers much of Burbank and Glendale. 
</P>
<P>
 Wilson set the election for May 3 with a runoff date of June 28, if needed. 
</P>
