<HEADLINE>
<P>
FREEWAY MONORAIL WOULD RISK LIVES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I was shocked to see the letter from County Supervisor Mike Antonovich (Feb. 
27), in which he is still promoting the idea of a monorail on the Ventura 
Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
 Perhaps he missed the earthquake we had on Jan. 17. I couldn't imagine the 
tragedy which would occur if an earthquake struck during a rush hour if a 
monorail were in place. Can you imagine several trains traveling at 60 or 70 
m.p.h. with hundreds of passengers on board being derailed and flying into 
hundreds of cars? 
</P>
<P>
 Let's not trade lives for dollars. 
</P>
<P>
 PAUL J. HARDER 
</P>
<P>
 Encino 
</P>
