<HEADLINE>
<P>
THANKS OFFERED FOR NEWSPAPER DELIVERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Thank you, Los Angeles Times and, in particular, our Times carrier. 
</P>
<P>
 On that awful Monday morning of Jan. 17, frightened beyond any fright we have 
ever felt, afraid to go back into our house and with dirty water, mud and rocks 
two feet deep rushing down our street, we were sitting in our car trying to 
decide what to do -- and who came riding by but our Times carrier? What a 
welcome, normal sight. 
</P>
<P>
 We later found out that a water tank, holding 500,000 gallons, had ruptured, 
causing the flood. For a week we had no electricity, water, only intermittent 
phone service, and of all impossible things, no mail service. Yet every morning 
by 5:30, there was our paper, our link with the outside world. 
</P>
<P>
 LILLIAN NEEDLEMAN 
</P>
<P>
 Granada Hills 
</P>
