<HEADLINE>
<P>
A THANK-YOU TO REVIEWERS FOR MUSICAL VOYAGES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 John Roos' pop music review of Irish harpist Kim Robertson's concert at Shade 
Tree ("World Tour -- With String Attached," March 2) is a critique that's done 
just right. Though I missed the concert (and too many others because travel is 
difficult), I did not miss it altogether: Roos' description was like an "out of 
body experience" (see Jim Washburn's story about "journeys into consciousness" 
in that same day's View section).While reading Roos' review, I could almost 
feel that I was there at the concert. 
</P>
<P>
 Previews, too, are much appreciated by this music lover in North County. Some 
have pushed me into going to concerts that have changed my life. One was 
Washburn's preview in January, 1993, of a Richard Thompson concert. "GO SEE 
HIM!," Washburn admonished. Another was Mike Boehm's interview in 1992 with 
Rosalie Sorrels. I might have skipped that concert, but the interview was too 
compelling. 
</P>
<P>
 Thanks, Calendar section, for my chance to "journey into concert(ness)." 
</P>
<P>
 BETTY GLASSER 
</P>
<P>
 Anaheim 
</P>
</TEXT>
