<HEADLINE>
<P>
IT'S OK TO BE STRAIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I read with outrage the letters from indignant readers who condemned "Ace 
Ventura: Pet Detective" as "homophobic" because the title character, after 
discovering he's kissed another man by mistake, runs to the shower to cleanse 
himself ("Hey, Ace, Homophobia's Not So Funny!," Feb. 26). This is not 
homophobic. 
</P>
<P>
 How dare the gay community expect straight people to enjoy kissing members of 
the same sex! No heterosexual could be expected to receive pleasure from 
kissing a person of the same sex -- no more than you'd expect a gay person to 
enjoy kissing the opposite sex. 
</P>
<P>
 I am constantly infuriated at the gay community's insistence that everyone is 
gay. It seems to me that the gay community, in their refusal to believe anyone 
could be straight, is exposing itself as "heterophobic." 
</P>
<P>
 One more thing: How come nobody pitched a fit when the exact same scene was 
played out during "The Crying Game," when a character discovered that the woman 
he'd been dating was really a man and ran straight to the bathroom to vomit? 
</P>
<P>
 JENNIFER WILLIAMSON 
</P>
<P>
 La Crescenta 
</P>
