<TEXT>
<P>
 Blockbuster May Have to Revise Viacom Offer: Blockbuster Entertainment Corp., 
fighting dissident shareholders over its $8-billion merger with cable company 
Viacom Inc., acknowledged that it may have to revise the deal to win 
stockholder approval. The giant video rental company made the statement in a 
court filing opposing a last-minute attempt by the dissident group to block the 
deal. Blockbuster would buy $1.25 billion of stock from Viacom, which would 
then use the cash in its $10-billion takeover of Paramount Communications Inc. 
Viacom's stock price fell during the bidding contest for Paramount, cutting 
into the value that Blockbuster stockholders would receive in the deal. 
</P>
