<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEEKEND TV; CHANNEL 13 TO FOCUS ON L.A. MARATHON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By N.F. MENDOZA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After spending the last few weekends feasting on the sights and Olympic sports 
of Norway, viewers can tune in to a sports event in their own back yard this 
weekend. KCOP-TV Channel 13 will provide marathon coverage of the 26.2-mile Los 
Angeles Marathon on Sunday.The station begins its telecast at 8 a.m. and will 
stay with it until 1 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Meanwhile, two new TV movies square off against each other at 9 p.m. Sunday. 
ABC's is "One More Mountain," starring Meredith Baxter as a woman who takes her 
family on the Oregon Trail, (7)(3)(10)(42). On CBS (2)(8), Peter Strauss stars 
in "Thicker Than Blood: The Larry McLinden Story," about a securities broker 
who fights for custody of a 5-year-old boy even though he is not the biological 
father. N.F. MENDOZA 
</P>
</TEXT>
