<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPECIAL ELECTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gov. Pete Wilson Friday called a special election for May 3 to fill the 
vacancy created in the 43rd Assembly District -- much of Burbank and Glendale 
-- when former Assemblyman Pat Nolan pleaded guilty to corruption and resigned. 
If needed, a runoff would be held June 28. 
</P>
