<TEXT>
<P>
 County residents looking to toss their old batteries, paint and pesticides, 
will get a chance to do so legally today at a Household Hazardous Waste Roundup 
in Calabasas. 
</P>
<P>
 The roundup, from 9 a.m. to 5 p.m. at the Calabasas Park Centre, was scheduled 
to encourage residents to dispose properly of household wastes such as leftover 
motor oil, acids and herbicides. 
</P>
<P>
 Each driver can dispose of up to five gallons or 50 pounds of waste and are 
asked to bring items labeled and in sturdy containers. 
</P>
