<HEADLINE>
<P>
BUS FIRM CHOSEN FOR TRIAL PROGRAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A bus company has been selected to operate a new countywide bus service 
scheduled to start this summer. 
</P>
<P>
 The Ventura County Transportation Commission on Friday approved a contract 
with Antelope Valley Transportation to operate buses in the federally funded 
trial bus program. 
</P>
<P>
 The program, called Ventura Intercity Service Transit Authority, or VISTA, is 
scheduled to start in July and run for up to two years. VISTA, designed as a 
commuter bus service to link Ventura County's 10 cities, is funded with $1.2 
million in federal and local funds. 
</P>
<P>
 Routes have not been mapped out, but the air-conditioned, coach-style buses 
are expected to make one or two stops in each city. SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</TEXT>
