<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; ZOO TO THROW OWN 42ND BIRTHDAY PARTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Santa Ana Zoo will celebrate its 42nd birthday with a party complete with 
clowns, music and ice cream today, a spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Each visitor will receive a free ice cream and activities will include face 
painting, children's crafts and a scavenger hunt.Each child who brings a 
birthday card will receive a free party favor. The party, which is free with 
zoo admission, will run from 11 a.m. to 1 p.m., spokeswoman Leslie Perovich 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The zoo, at 1801 E. Chestnut Ave., is open daily from 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. 
Admission is $3 for adults, $1 for children under 12 and senior citizens, and 
free to the disabled. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call Perovich at (714) 953-8555.JON NALICK 
</P>
</TEXT>
