<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE TO GO DOOR-TO-DOOR IN SHOOTING PROBE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police are planning a door-to-door search today to investigate two incidents 
during the past week in which moving cars were the targets of gunfire in the 
8600 block of Moody Street. One person was injured in the attacks. 
</P>
<P>
 Both incidents took place at 5 a.m. in the northbound lanes of Moody just 
south of Crescent Avenue, Cypress Police Lt. John Schaefer said. 
</P>
<P>
 A 55-year-old man driving northbound on Moody on Friday was wounded when a 
bullet passed through the driver's side door of his vehicle and struck him in 
the thigh, police said. He was taken to Los Alamitos General Hospital for 
treatment. 
</P>
<P>
 On Monday, a 43-year-old woman who had heard a noise while driving on Moody 
later found a bullet hole in the rear door of the driver's side of her vehicle, 
police said. 
</P>
