</P>
<P>
 Male: 73%  
</P>
<P>
 Female: 27% 
</P>
<P>
 Number who entered in '93: 19,122 
</P>
<P>
 Number who finished: 14,546 
</P>
<P>
 Nations represented: 93 
</P>
<P>
 States represented: 48 (all except North Dakota and Vermont) Entrants by Age 
17 and under: 442 18-29: 3,390 30-39: 4,785 40-49: 3,336 50-59: 1,397 60-69: 
403 70-79: 59 80 and over: 4 By Education High school: 17% College: 57% 
Graduate school: 25% Top 10 Professions 1. Students: 1,307 2. 
Administrators/managers: 1,001 3. Teachers/educators: 796 4. Engineers: 785 5. 
Lawyers: 438 6. Accountants: 421 7. Salespeople: 406 8. Business owners: 401 9. 
Physicians: 352 10. Homemakers: 252 REFERENCE MAP (Starting Line Spectators) 
</P>
<P>
 Family and friends should watch the start of the race from the east side of 
Figueroa and north of Exposition. THE START 
</P>
<P>
 Runners should reach the starting line by 8:15. They must line up in one of 
two "blocks," according to their race numbers. 
</P>
<P>
