<HEADLINE>
<P>
SWIMMING / PAC-10 FINALS; STANFORD STAYS AHEAD OF PACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Stanford men's swim team continued to dominate the Pacific 10 Conference 
championships at the Belmont Plaza Pool in Long Beach on Friday, winning six of 
seven events and increasing its lead over second-place UCLA. 
</P>
<P>
 Stanford has accumulated 696 points, 276 ahead of UCLA and 324 ahead of 
third-place USC with today's six events remaining. 
</P>
<P>
 The only event the Cardinal failed to win Friday was the 100-yard butterfly, 
won by Arizona's Martin Pepper in 47.60 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
 The Cardinal took first through fifth places in the 200 freestyle. Sophomore 
Joe Hudepohl retained his Pac-10 title, finishing in 1 minute 35.67 seconds. It 
was Hudepohl's second individual title of the meet. He won the 50 free Thursday 
night. Stanford's Derek Weatherford also won his second title, the 100 
backstroke in 46.92, the fastest time in the nation this season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
