<P>
BASEBALL / DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE MAJOR LEAGUES; JORDAN GROUNDS TO MOUND IN 
DEBUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Michael Jordan made his much-awaited debut in a major league exhibition game 
for the Chicago White Sox at Sarasota, Fla., and in his only at-bat, chopped a 
ball back to the pitcher and was tagged out. He played four innings in a 9-0 
loss to the Texas Rangers, and had only one play in right field, picking up a 
double and making a one-hop relay to the infield. . . . The Pittsburgh Pirates 
need an emergency bailout of $8 million during the next year to stay in 
business, Mayor Tom Murphy said. 
</P>
