<HEADLINE>
<P>
BANNING USES A BIG SECOND HALF TO BEAT GARDENA FOR 3-A GIRLS' TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ARA NAJARIAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jenille Ramos scored 14 of her game-high 20 points in the second half to lead 
Wilmington Banning to a 47-32 victory over Gardena in the City Section Division 
3-A girls' basketball championship game at the Sports Arena Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Banning led, 19-18, at halftime and increased the margin to 28-24 after three 
quarters behind Ramos' seven third-quarter points. 
</P>
<P>
 A minute into the fourth quarter, Ramos scored on a fast-break layup and a 
three-point basket to give Banning (16-11) a commanding 33-24 lead. Gardena 
(17-7) never recovered. 
</P>
<P>
 "We came out nervous -- we've never been in a place like this -- but we got to 
halftime and I said, 'OK, we got the jitters out, now we can get it going,' " 
Banning Coach David DeLaby said. 
</P>
<P>
 Gardena never got its offense going in the second half, in part because of 
Banning's pressure defense. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was Gardena's first time in the finals for either boys' or girls' 
basketball," Gardena Coach Cheryl Nakata said. "So we're proud regardless." 
</P>
<P>
 Tiwana McCullum led the Mohicans with 12 points. ARA NAJARIAN 
</P>
