<P>
HENSON'S 29 POINTS PACE BASSETT TO A 77-73 VICTORY OVER ST. PAUL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BARRY BAUM 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Robert Henson scored a game-high 29 points before fouling out with 3:21 to 
play as La Puente Bassett High defeated Sante Fe Springs St. Paul, 77-73, in 
the Southern Section Division IV-AA championship game at UC Irvine's Bren 
Center Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Bassett (16-12) won its first-ever section title, but the victory did not come 
easily.Before the Olympians knew what hit them, they trailed, 21-9, late in the 
first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 "We were very concerned," Henson said. "We had to pick up our defense." 
</P>
<P>
 Henson, a 6-foot-5 senior, led the charge back as Bassett outscored St. Paul, 
13-2, and took a 42-37 lead by halftime. Henson scored 16 of his 22 first-half 
points in the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Emmery Thompson led Bassett in the second half, scoring 17 of his 28 points. 
</P>
<P>
 After trailing by 14 going into the fourth quarter, the Swordsmen cut their 
deficit to 72-71 with 1:19 to play. But Bassett hit five of seven free throws 
in the final minute to clinch the title. 
</P>
<P>
 Jason Reynolds led St. Paul (16-12) with 22 points. BARRY BAUM 
</P>
