<P>
HIGH SCHOOL GIRLS' BASKETBALL PLAYOFFS; CRENSHAW TOPS ROOSEVELT IN OT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LONNIE WHITE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Shannon Burton scored five points and Kimberly Howse added four in the second 
overtime to give Crenshaw High a 75-68 victory over Roosevelt in the City 
Division 4-A championship Friday at the Sports Arena. 
</P>
<P>
 Howse, who also scored four points in the first overtime, finished with a 
team-high 19 points as Crenshaw (22-5) won its second consecutive City 
title.The Cougars defeated North Hollywood in last year's championship game. 
</P>
<P>
 "We play a lot of games when we started off rough," said Howse, a six-foot 
senior. "But once it gets into the second half, it's all over. We could have 
gone into five overtimes, we weren't going to lose." 
</P>
<P>
 Roosevelt (21-2) had sent the game into overtime by outscoring the Cougars, 
10-1, in the final three minutes of regulation, with Zenobia Tyson-Hunt scoring 
on a turnaround jump shot to tie the score, 60-60. 
</P>
<P>
 In the first overtime, Crenshaw held a 65-63 lead with five seconds remaining 
before Roosevelt's Denise Caudillo tied the score with a layup at the buzzer. 
Caudillo, a three-time all-city performer, finished with a game-high 30 points. 
LONNIE WHITE 
