<P>
HIGH SCHOOL SOCCER CHAMPIONSHIPS; TOP-RANKED MARINA GIRLS SHUT OUT PENINSULA 
FOR TITLE, 3-0 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PETER BARZILAI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Huntington Beach Marina girls' soccer team, ranked No. 1 in the state, won 
the Southern Section Division I championship Friday, defeating Palos Verdes 
Peninsula, 3-0, at Gahr High.  
</P>
<P>
 The victory gave the top-seeded Vikings (28-0-1) their second consecutive 
title.Last season, Marina was co-champion with Claremont. 
</P>
<P>
 Amy Rubenstein opened the scoring in the 38th minute. The goal came off a 
corner kick after Peninsula had several opportunities to clear the ball. 
</P>
<P>
 In boys' games: 
</P>
<P>
 Claremont 2, Upland 0 -- The Wolfpack's Jason Christensen scored on a rebound 
when Colby Jackson's free kick bounced off the crossbar in the 45th minute.  
</P>
<P>
 The free kick came after Upland goalie Philip Teague was given a red card for 
intentionally taking down Dejan Nagl on a breakaway. 
</P>
<P>
 Jackson later scored on a breakaway.  
</P>
<P>
 Claremont is 19-6-4, Upland 21-5-4. 
</P>
<P>
 Calabasas 1, Moorpark 1 -- After tying during the regular season, the Frontier 
League opponents tied again in the Division V title game and were named 
co-champions. 
</P>
<P>
 Herbie Sirota scored in the ninth minute for Calabasas (13-3-3). 
</P>
<P>
 Patrick Russo tied it early in the second half for Moorpark (26-2-2). PETER 
BARZILAI 
