<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; NO. 4 DANA HILLS UPSETS NO. 1 OILERS IN BOYS' VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Behind some strong blocking, Dana Hills upset top-ranked Huntington Beach, 
15-5, 16-14, 15-13, in a nonleague boys' volleyball match Friday at Huntington 
Beach High. 
</P>
<P>
 Matt Clem had nine kills and eight blocks, and Neil Hewko had nine kills and 
five blocks for the Dolphins (2-0), ranked fourth in the Orange County 
preseason poll. 
</P>
<P>
 Jeremy Darner added 10 kills and Bob Hefty had seven kills and five blocks for 
Dana Hills (2-0). 
</P>
<P>
 Mike Grave and Nick Ziegler each had six kills for the host Oilers (0-1), the 
defending Southern Section Division I champions who finished 23-0 last season. 
MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
