<P>
CLU TO FACE UC SAN DIEGO IN DIVISION III PLAYOFF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN ORTEGA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cal Lutheran will play at UC San Diego in a second-round game of the NCAA 
Division III men's basketball playoffs at 7:30 tonight. 
</P>
<P>
 The Kingsmen (24-2), co-champions of the Southern California Intercollegiate 
Athletic Conference, had a first-round bye Thursday while UC San Diego defeated 
SCIAC co-champion Pomona-Pitzer, 67-66. 
</P>
<P>
 The winner of tonight's game will play the winner of a game between Greensboro 
(N.C.) and Christopher Newport (Va.) in a sectional semifinal Mar. 11. 
</P>
<P>
 Cal Lutheran defeated UC San Diego, 100-79, in a nonconference game this 
season, but the Tritons (21-4) have won 15 of 16 since. 
</P>
<P>
 The Kingsmen have won four in a row, including last Saturday's 83-62 win over 
Pomona-Pitzer which gave Cal Lutheran the SCIAC's automatic playoff berth. JOHN 
ORTEGA 
</P>
