<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL LAZARUS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The signs are good for the Campbell Hall High boys' basketball team. 
</P>
<P>
 The Vikings play Pasadena Poly for the Southern Section Division I 
championship at 7:30 tonight at Pepperdine's Firestone Fieldhouse.In 1992, when 
the Vikings won the V-AA championship, the final was played at Pepperdine. 
</P>
<P>
 Campbell Hall (20-8) defeated Delphic League rival Faith Baptist in the title 
game that year. The Vikings advanced to the championship game this season by 
defeating league rival Brentwood, 62-60, Tuesday night. 
</P>
<P>
 In 1992, the Vikings beat Pasadena Poly in the second round of the playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 "As the home team, we got to choose the site," Campbell Hall Coach Jon Palarz 
said. "Hopefully, it will bring us the same kind of success." 
</P>
<P>
 After sneaking into the playoffs as the Delphic's third-place team, the 
Vikings are playing their best basketball of the season. But to stop Pasadena 
Poly (21-4), the Vikings must thwart the front line of Cameron Murphy and 
brothers Scott and Rob Reeder, all of whom are at least 6-foot-5. 
</P>
<P>
 The Vikings, however, have the biggest player on the court in 6-foot-10 center 
Alex Lopez. Senior swingmen Simeon Woodall and Harold Sylvester complement 
Lopez with solid outside shooting. MICHAEL LAZARUS 
</P>
</TEXT>
