<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: GREMINGER RESIGNS AFTER 25 YEARS AS AGOURA COACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Agoura High football Coach Frank Greminger announced his resignation Friday 
after a 25-year career at the school. 
</P>
<P>
 Greminger, 55, had a record of 154-99-3 and led the Chargers to five Frontier 
League titles and a Southern Section Desert-Mountain Conference championship in 
1984.He will continue to coach the Chargers' golf team and teach physical 
education. 
</P>
<P>
 Agoura Athletic Director John Crow said applications for Greminger's successor 
will be accepted at the Las Virgenes Unified School District office. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's kind of a sad day," Crow said. "How he stayed in that long is beyond 
me." 
</P>
<P>
 Crow said Greminger, who could not be reached for comment, had tired of the 
time commitments required by football. 
</P>
<P>
 Greminger missed a game last season because of chest pains, checking into a 
hospital the day of a game against Santa Barbara. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Dan Lazarovits of Taft High committed to play football next season at Cal 
State Northridge. 
</P>
<P>
 Lazarovits, a 6-foot-4, 245-pound senior, played linebacker and offensive line 
at Taft, but Northridge wants to convert him into a defensive lineman, which is 
fine with Lazarovits. 
</P>
<P>
 "I felt CSUN has faith in me. They wanted to invest in me," Lazarovits said. 
"They want me to come over and make an impact." 
</P>
<P>
 Lazarovits, a two-time All-City Section selection, made no other official 
recruiting trips. High School Soccer  
</P>
<P>
 The City Section boys' and girls' soccer championships, which had been 
scheduled at East Los Angeles College today, have been moved to Birmingham 
High. 
</P>
<P>
 The girls' match between Grant and San Pedro will start at noon. 
</P>
<P>
 Bell and Belmont will play in the boys' final at 2 p.m. Bowling  
</P>
<P>
 Eric Forkel of Chatsworth qualified fourth for today's stepladder finals of 
the Professional Bowlers Assn. $175,000 National Championship at Toledo, Ohio. 
The finals will be televised by KABC-TV beginning at 3 p.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
