Harbor, 72-40, in one semifinal of the community college women's basketball 
State tournament Friday at Solano College in Suisun City. 
</P>
<P>
 The Pirates had beaten San Mateo, 68-57, Thursday in the quarterfinal 
round.OCC came into the tournament as the third-place team from the Orange 
Empire Conference. San Mateo was the top-ranked team in the State for the last 
two months. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles Harbor (30-6) moves into the 8 p.m. title game against Golden 
West. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Coast shot 20% (5 of 25) in the first half and fell behind, 43-18. 
LeAnn Kazmer, a sophomore forward, was the only Orange Coast player in double 
figures with 13 points. 
