<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE WOMEN'S BASKETBALL STATE TOURNAMENT; GOLDEN WEST STARTS FAST, 
HOLDS OFF BUTTE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nicole Quinn scored off an offensive rebound as time ran out to give Golden 
West a 65-64 victory over Butte in a semifinal game of the women's basketball 
State tournament Friday at Solano College in Suisun City. 
</P>
<P>
 Butte took its only lead, 64-63, when Michelle Hearn scored with 12 seconds 
left.Quinn, daughter of Saddleback High boys' basketball Coach Pat Quinn, made 
the winning shot after Butte's Iseth Cowan (26 points) got a rebound but lost 
the ball. 
</P>
<P>
 "I didn't realize the basket counted until my teammates hugged me," Quinn 
said. "I thought time had run out." 
</P>
<P>
 Golden West was at its best early, opening a 31-9 lead. The Rustlers led, 
39-22, at the half but Butte rallied in the second half, outscoring the 
Rustlers, 42-26. 
</P>
<P>
 Julie Murdent scored 23 and Michelle Kravik added 12 and Deana Itow had 11 and 
eight assists. Kristin Brun had a team-high 11 rebounds and six assists. 
</P>
<P>
 Golden West (33-4) is playing in its eighth consecutive State tournament. The 
Rustlers won titles in 1990 and 1991. Golden West advances to play L.A. Harbor 
in the title game at 8 tonight. 
</P>
