 OVERALL: 18-10-1 
</P>
<P>
 LEAGUE: 11-3 
</P>
<P>
 COACH: Chris Pascal 
</P>
<P>
 RECORD AT SCHOOL: 123-95-3 04,20,05,06,05 RETURNING STARTERS YR. POS. B-T 
Chris Clark Sr. P/SS R-R Charlie Marino Jr. OF R-R Kenny Sundstrom Sr. Inf L-R 
04,16,05,07,05 TOP RETURNERS YR. POS. B-T Josh McDaniel Sr. Inf/P S-R Wes 
Morris Sr. OF L-L Aaron Peardon Sr. OF R-R Steve Robinett Sr. C R-R 
04,16,05,06,05 TOP NEWCOMERS YR. POS. B-T Joe Zannitto Sr. P R-R Alex Garcia 
Sr. Inf R-R Jake Koziel Jr. OF R-R Rich Sundstrom Jr. Inf R-R Jeff Tow Jr. P 
R-R OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 Kennedy has won or shared two consecutive Garden Grove League titles. If the 
Fighting Irish are going to win a third, they will have to find two pitchers to 
go with Clark (7-3), a first-team all-league pitcher the past two years. 
Zannitto and Tow are the candidates, but they are unproven. McDaniel is the 
only pitcher, other than Clark, with varsity experience and he threw one inning 
last season. "If Clark has to throw too many innings, he could wear down," 
Pascal said. Pascal is counting on his team's speed wearing down opponents. 
"We're going to have to run to make some things happen," he said. Center 
fielder Morris and left fielder Marino, a second-team all-league player, will 
do most of the running. Shortstop is another question mark. McDaniel, Clark and 
Garcia all could play there. "Clark started last year, but I'd like to take one 
guy and leave him there," Pascal said. 
</P>
