<P>
 COACH: Vern Nelson 
</P>
<P>
 RECORD AT SCHOOL: 177-212-5 04,20,05,06,05 RETURNING STARTERS YR. POS. B-T 
Tony Alcorn Sr. LF R-R Brian Baughman Sr. 3B-P R-R Alex Francisco Sr. SS R-R 
Kevin Michini Sr. OF R-R Bryan Moore Sr. P R-R Alex Navarro So. 1B L-R Rony 
Ralpho Sr. 2B R-R 04,17,05,07,05 TOP RETURNERS YR. POS. B-T Brent Caldwell Sr. 
P-1B R-R Anthony Gomez Sr. P R-R Andrew Gonzalez Sr. Util. R-R Ed Hallowell Sr. 
Util. R-R 04,17,05,06,05 TOP NEWCOMERS YR. POS. B-T Dan Hendrix So. C R-R Jaime 
Lua Sr. OF R-R Glen Strzelecki Sr. OF R-R OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 Seven starters, six of them seniors, return from last year's last-place team. 
The experienced, but not flashy, group has Nelson excited. "We may not have the 
best athletes; we don't have anything to draw scouts," he said, "but this is 
the best group we've had in a long time. I think they'll play together. I think 
we'll surprise people. The last championship we won at Bolsa (in 1984) was with 
the kind of team we have right here." The team's unmistakable leader is 
Baughman, a first-team all-league player in football and basketball. "The next 
day after basketball ended, he's out here leading everybody," Nelson said. 
Baughman, who led the county in passing yardage this year, hasn't pitched since 
his freshman season, but he will be Nelson's ace this year. "If we'd have 
pitched him the last two years, we could have done some damage to his 
shoulder." 
</P>
