<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP BASEBALL '94: GARDEN GROVE LEAGUE; GARDEN GROVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 1993 RECORDS 
</P>
<P>
 OVERALL: 15-7-1 
</P>
<P>
 LEAGUE: 7-7 
</P>
<P>
 COACH: Jim Rawls 
</P>
<P>
 RECORD AT SCHOOL: 128-109-2 04,20,05,06,05 RETURNING STARTERS YR. POS. B-T 
Justin Lewis Sr. OF R-R Ron Moreno Sr. P L-L 04,15,05,06,05 TOP RETURNERS YR. 
POS. B-T Kevin Loken Jr. 3B-C R-R Carlos Onofre Sr. DH R-R Greg Pines So. 3B-C 
R-R Jon Snavely Sr. 1B R-R 04,16,05,06,05 TOP NEWCOMERS YR. POS. B-T Adam Bass 
Jr. INF R-R Mike Campuzano Jr. OF-P L-L Brian Jones So. OF L-L Jose Peraza Sr. 
INF R-R Jared Sernir Jr. INF R-R Jeff Van Horne Jr. OF R-R OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 The Argonauts have gone 31-15-1 the past two seasons, but the party appears to 
be over for Rawls. Five players return from last season's team and only Moreno 
(7-4, 2.47 ERA) and Lewis (.309, 12 RBIs) were starters. Rawls said he probably 
will start five sophomores. "The team we had the past three years started as 
sophomores," Rawls said. "So we're definitely trying to build something here 
for the future. I just wish we had a big-time pitcher waiting in the wings, 
like Kennedy and La Quinta, to make the transition easier, but we don't." Rawls 
said his inexperienced team will have to rely on consistency, tough defense and 
timely hitting. "Without a dominant pitcher, we'll have to play mistake-free 
baseball," he said. Since most of his players were on junior varsity and 
freshman teams last year, Rawls said he doesn't know what to expect from his 
offense. "The hitting is all untested," he said. "I have no idea what they'll 
do." 
</P>
