<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP BASEBALL '94: GARDEN GROVE LEAGUE; LOS AMIGOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 1993 RECORDS 
</P>
<P>
 OVERALL: 5-18 
</P>
<P>
 LEAGUE: 4-10 
</P>
<P>
 COACH: Steve Foreman 
</P>
<P>
 RECORD AT SCHOOL: 0-0 04,20,05,06,05 RETURNING STARTERS YR. POS. B-T Adam 
Elsaesser Sr. P R-R Josh Hoover Sr. C R-R Shawn Locher Sr. OF R-R Jeff 
Rutherford Sr. P R-R TOP RETURNERS: None 04,19,05,06,05 TOP NEWCOMERS YR. POS. 
B-T Fernando Bustos Jr. INF R-R Gilbert Contreras Jr. INF R-R Caesar Garcia So. 
INF R-L Mike Garcia So. INF R-R OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 Foreman, who took over for Ron Pruter, has begun his new job by essentially 
cleaning house. He cut four of eight seniors, and has chosen to build with 
juniors and sophomores. "I'm starting a three-year plan to gain experience for 
the next year," Foreman said. "We're promoting a positive attitude. The 
attitude has been down here for so long. I'll be satisfied if we go .500 this 
season." Foreman plans to build around his pitching, which will be led by 
Rutherford. "He was on the wild side last year, but we've worked on his 
mechanics," Foreman said. "He's developed two new pitches and he's more 
positive." Elsaesser will be the No. 2 pitcher and Contreras, a junior varsity 
catcher last season, will be No. 3. "(Elsaesser) was strictly a fastball 
pitcher last year, but now he has a slider and a split," Foreman said. 
"(Contreras) loves it. He's throwing smoke. He's 6-4 and has a cannon." While 
Los Amigos' pitching might be strong, the Lobos' offensive attack figures to be 
shaky. "We'll bunt and run because we've got speed, but pitching will keep us 
in the ball game," Foreman said. "Hoover and Bustos are the only power we've 
got." 
</P>
