<P>
 Crespi lost a lot of players from last year's team that made it to the 
Division I semifinals, but the Celts' offense remains intact. Crespi has three 
of the area's best hitters in Wright, Farlow and Glendenning. Wright, a 
left-hander, batted .420 last season with 22 RBIs. Wright, an All-Southern 
Section pick, also will play in the outfield. Farlow, a left-hander and an 
all-league selection, hit .375 with 23 RBIs. Glendenning sat out last season 
because he was academically ineligible, but he is an impact player who is 
expected to be drafted in June. Clemons didn't pitch much last season, but is 
the top hurler. He went 2-0 with a 2.88 ERA two years ago. Harvard-Westlake 
